
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `colormgr` (Color Manager) baraye modiriat rang-ha va profile-haye rang dar system-e shoma estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta rang-haye dorost va motabeg baraye dastgah-haye mokhtalef (mesle monitor-ha, printer-ha va scanner-ha) ra be kar beرید.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `colormgr devices`  --> 🖥️ List kardan hameye dastgah-haye rang shenasayi shode.
    🔹 `colormgr get-devices`  --> ➕ Gereftan list dastgah ha, hamanand `devices`.
    🔹 `colormgr device-info ID`  --> ℹ️ Namayesh etela'at darbarye yek dastgah be khosos ba estefade az ID an.
    🔹 `colormgr import-profile FILE` --> 📦 Import kardan yek profile rang az file.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ colormgr devices

    🔹 Namayesh list dastgah-haye rangshenasayi shode.

    $ colormgr device-info display_samsung_SyncMaster_2494HM

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at darbarye dastgah ba ID "display_samsung_SyncMaster_2494HM".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ colormgr get-devices

    🔹 Listi az device ha ro neshon mide. in dastoor be shoma ID-haye dastgah ha ro mide ke betoonid ba 'device-info' estefade konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `colormgr` (Color Manager) command is used to manage color profiles on your system. It helps ensure accurate and consistent colors for different devices such as monitors, printers, and scanners.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `colormgr devices`  --> 🖥️ List all detected color devices.
    🔹 `colormgr get-devices`  --> ➕ Retrieve a list of devices, similar to `devices`.
    🔹 `colormgr device-info ID`  --> ℹ️ Display information about a specific device using its ID.
    🔹 `colormgr import-profile FILE` --> 📦 Import a color profile from a file.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ colormgr devices

    🔹 Display the list of detected color devices.

    $ colormgr device-info display_samsung_SyncMaster_2494HM

    🔹 Display information about the device with the ID "display_samsung_SyncMaster_2494HM".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ colormgr get-devices

    🔹 Shows a list of available color devices. This command gives you the device IDs you can use with the `device-info` command to learn more about a particular device.
